        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 5. The shifted exponential distribution has the density function "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                139,
                105,
                789,
                124
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "f (y; \\phi , \\theta) = 1 / \\theta \\exp \\{- (u - \\phi) / \\theta \\}, \\qquad y > \\phi , \\theta > 0.",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/72be9b1e2fb9400709efa65b0da37a5468182b9709eaa1f16332efa2db454e8e.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                302,
                141,
                747,
                160
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "Y _ { 1 } , \\dots , Y _ { n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be a random sample from this distribution. Find the maximum likelihood estimator (MLE) of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\phi"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\theta"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and the limiting distribution of the MLE. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                175,
                907,
                212
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "You may use the following R´enyi representation of the order statistics: Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "E _ { 1 } , \\ldots , E _ { n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", be a random sample from the standard exponential distribution (i.e., the above distribution with "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\phi = 0 , \\theta = 1"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "). Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "E _ { ( r ) }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "denote the "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "r"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "-th order statistics. According to the R´enyi representation, "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                137,
                216,
                910,
                294
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "E _ {(r)} \\stackrel {D} {=} \\sum_ {j = 1} ^ {r} \\frac {E _ {j}}{n + 1 - j}, \\qquad r = 1, \\ldots , n.",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/3a3e3a884be24b533fd20996ce910342f4da70dff08dc551b197b9b28b29390d.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                357,
                294,
                690,
                340
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Here, the symbol "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\underline { { \\underline { { D } } } }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "denotes equal in distribution. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                139,
                347,
                571,
                368
            ]
        }
